name: welcome message
tID: Welcome, Challenger! Complete the Training Camp to unlock the multiplayer Arena.

name: winning condition1
tID: Destroy more Crown Towers than your opponent to win!

name: winning condition2
tID: Destroy the enemy King's tower to get an instant victory!

name: elixir basics1
tID: Elixir generates automatically during battle. Playing a card costs Elixir.

name: elixir basics2
tID: Save your Elixir to play multiple cards at once.

name: elixir basics3
tID: Play multiple cards together to create a stronger push.

name: exp level1
tID: Your King Level indicates the strength of your King Tower and Princess Towers.

name: exp level2
tID: Increase your King Level by upgrading cards and donating cards to your Clanmates.

name: battle basics1
tID: Big troops are vulnerable to groups of small troops.

name: battle basics2
tID: Groups of small troops are vulnerable to area damage.

name: join clan1
tID: Join a Clan for card requests, Friendly Battles and fun!

name: join clan2
tID: Join a Clan for card requests, Friendly Battles and CLAN WARS!

name: tv royale
tID: TV Royale contains some of the best games played recently. Watch and learn!

name: arrows
tID: Use Arrows to stop a group of small troops.

name: giant
tID: Giants target buildings and ignore enemy troops.

name: knight and archers
tID: The Knight followed by Archers is a simple and effective strategy.

name: area damage
tID: Some troops deal area damage, hitting multiple units at once.

name: match duration
tID: Each battle can last three minutes, possibly extended by a minute of sudden death tiebreaker.

name: overtime
tID: During Sudden Death, the first player to take down a tower wins!

name: card types
tID: There are three types of card: Troops, Buildings and Spells.

name: card rarities
tID: Cards come in four levels of rarity: Common, Rare, Epic and Legendary.

name: deck basics1
tID: Balance your Battle Deck with cards that can target both ground and air.

name: deck basics2
tID: You can take 8 cards from your collection into battle. This is your Battle Deck.

name: clan rewards
tID: Donating cards to your Clanmates earns gold and increases your King Level.

name: king activation
tID: The King only joins the fight after taking damage or losing a Crown Tower.

name: king daughters
tID: The Princesses protect the King from atop their Crown Towers.

name: story1
tID: Goblins only joined the Arena after their union signed a lucrative deal with the Royales.

name: building lifetime
tID: All buildings slowly lose \qHitpoints\q, expiring after a set amount of time.

name: crown towers
tID: All Crown Towers target both ground and air troops.

name: building targeting
tID: Some defensive buildings only target ground troops, while others target both ground and air.

name: card upgrades
tID: Upgrading cards makes them more powerful, but their Elixir cost remains the same.

name: card unlocks
tID: Gain Trophies to enter new Arenas, which give access to new cards!

name: card shop
tID: The selection of cards available in the Shop refreshes every 24 hours.

name: chest basics1
tID: Rarer chests contain more cards and gold.

name: chest basics2
tID: Higher Arena chests contain more cards and gold.

name: chest basics3
tID: Gold Chests always contain at least one Rare Card.

name: chest basics4
tID: Magical Chests always contain at least one Epic Card.

name: chest_basics5
tID: The Crown Chest contains cards based on your current Arena.

name: matchmaking
tID: Your opponents are selected based on your Trophy count.

name: bomb tower
tID: Bomb Towers are good against groups of small troops.

name: tank1
tID: Support durable troops by deploying ranged troops behind them.

name: tank2
tID: Protect squishy troops by deploying durable troops in front of them.

name: prince
tID: Prince deals double damage to the first target he strikes while charging.

name: tesla
tID: Tesla cannot be damaged while underground, and only pops up when enemy troops are in range.

name: deploy area
tID: You can deploy on your opponent's side of the Arena after destroying one of their Crown Towers.

name: taunts
tID: Use Emotes to show your opponent you're a good sport!

name: three crowns
tID: Sometimes it's worth pushing for a 3-Crown victory. Sometimes securing two Crowns is the smarter play.

name: balloon
tID: The Balloon drops a bomb when destroyed. Don't stand still.

name: double elixir
tID: Elixir production is doubled during the final 60 seconds.

name: huts
tID: The Goblin Hut and Barbarian Hut spawn troops periodically.

name: tombstone
tID: The Tombstone releases a group of Skeletons when destroyed.

name: rage
tID: The Rage Spell increases movement and attack speed.

name: direct damage
tID: Damage spells like the Fireball deal reduced damage to Crown Towers.

name: elixir basics4
tID: 10 Elixir is the maximum you can hold.

name: starting hand
tID: During battle, your starting cards are randomly selected from your Battle Deck.

name: crown chest
tID: Every 24 hours you can collect 10 Crowns to unlock the Crown Chest.

name: pro1
tID: Lure troops to your side of the Arena to engage them with your Crown Towers.

name: pro2
tID: Using Elixir efficiently is the key to victory.

name: pro3
tID: X-Bows and Mortars can directly damage your opponent's Crown Towers if positioned near the middle.

name: pro4
tID: Giants can be effective on defense, too.

name: pro5
tID: Sometimes not playing a card is the best play to make. Don't waste Elixir!

name: targeting
tID: When deployed, all troops march towards the enemy King, attacking their preferred targets along the way.

name: inferno
tID: The Inferno Tower's damage increases over time while attacking the same target.

name: giant skeleton
tID: The Giant Skeleton carries a large bomb, which he carelessly drops when destroyed. Oops!

name: epic sunday
tID: Collect a free Epic Card from the Shop every Sunday!

name: hog rider
tID: Hog Riders can jump over the river.

name: golem1
tID: Golems target buildings and ignore troops.

name: golem2
tID: The Golem explodes when destroyed and splits into two smaller Golemites.

name: golem3
tID: Golem has a heart made of stone.

name: pekkas
tID: The P.E.K.K.A and Mini P.E.K.K.A are easily distracted, but they hit like a truck.

name: trophy count
tID: Trophies that you win are deducted from your opponent's Trophies!

name: lightning
tID: Experts have long believed that lightning is attracted to tall objects, however, new research indicates that lightning is, in fact, attracted to high hitpoints.

name: bomber
tID: One day, Wall Breakers realized that they could do a lot more damage if they THREW the bomb instead of sat beside it. Imagine that...

name: pekka
tID: P.E.K.K.A: No-one knows what's behind that mask. Maybe even another mask.

name: wizard
tID: The Wizard can control all elements, except his hair.

name: friendly battles1
tID: In Friendly Battles, Sudden Death lasts for 3 minutes to minimize draws.

name: friendly battles2
tID: In Friendly Battles, all cards and towers are level 9.

name: friendly battles4
tID: All cards and towers are level 9 in Friendly Battles.

name: tourney battles1
tID: All cards and towers are capped at level 9 in Challenges and Tournaments.

name: tourney battles2
tID: In Challenges and Tournaments, all cards and towers are capped at level 9.

name: legendary chest1
tID: Legendary Chests contain a Legendary Card from any Arena!

name: legendary chest2
tID: Legendary Chests can be won from battle, but they're incredibly rare!

name: super magical chest1
tID: Super Magical Chests have a high chance of containing a Legendary Card.

name: super magical chest2
tID: Super Magical Chests can be won from battle, but they're incredibly rare!

name: giant chest1
tID: Giant Chests can be won from battle, but they're quite rare!

name: giant chest2
tID: Giant Chests contain a huge amount of Common and Rare Cards, but few Epic Cards.

name: three musketeers
tID: Three Musketeers pack triple the punch of one, at a little over double the cost. Value!

name: dark prince
tID: Break the Dark Prince's shield first, then you can start to whittle down his hitpoints.

name: ice wizard
tID: Despite the Ice Wizard being freezing cold, he has a handlebar mustache that's too hot for TV.

name: princess
tID: If you're feeling warm feelings towards the Princess, it's probably because you're on fire.

name: royal giant
tID: Royal Giants target buildings from range and ignore enemy troops.

name: poison
tID: Poison covers the area in a deadly toxin, damaging enemy troops and buildings over time.

name: gold per win
tID: You receive gold for each win, even when your chest slots are full.

name: lava hound
tID: The Lava Hound is a majestic flying beast. The Lava Pups are less majestic angry babies.

name: miner
tID: The Miner can burrow his way underground and appear anywhere in the Arena. It's not magic, it's a shovel.

name: sparky
tID: Overkill isn't in Sparky's vocabulary.

name: legendary card
tID: Legendary Cards can appear in your Shop once you've reached Arena 10.

name: bowler
tID: The Bowler is a big blue dude who digs the simple things in life - Dark Elixir drinks and throwing rocks.

name: rage log
tID: The Lumberjack and The Log go way back...

name: tourney2
tID: Challenges and Tournaments unlock at King Level 5 - check out the Events tab!

name: tourney3
tID: Challenges and Tournaments are played with cards and towers capped at level 9.

name: tourney4
tID: You can play in one Challenge and one Tournaments at a time.

name: tourney5
tID: Every win in a Challenge increases your reward!

name: tourney6
tID: A Challenge ends at either 12 wins or 3 losses - whichever comes first.

name: tourney7
tID: In a Challenge, your opponents are selected based on your current wins in that Challenge.

name: tourney8
tID: In a Tournament, your opponents are selected based on your Tournament Trophy count.

name: tourney9
tID: Spectate Tournament games by tapping the \qeye\q icon on the tournament leaderboard.

name: arena pack
tID: When you reach a new Arena, a special one time \qArena Value Pack\q will be available to purchase from the Shop.

name: friends list1
tID: Challenge your friends to a Friendly Battle from the friends list!

name: friends list2
tID: You can see when friends are online and spectate their battles from the friends list.

name: mute1
tID: You can mute your opponent during battle from the Emote button.

name: mute2
tID: If you don't like seeing Emotes, you can permanently mute them from the Emote button.

name: epic chest
tID: Epic Chests can be won from battle, but they're incredibly rare!

name: graveyard
tID: The Graveyard spell starts a surprise Skeleton party anywhere in the Arena. Yay!

name: clone
tID: You can't Clone a Clone.

name: bandit
tID: The Bandit cannot be hit while dashing.

name: sparky2
tID: Calling Sparky a \qtrash can on wheels\q hurts her feelings.

name: 2v2 1
tID: 2v2 Battle allows you to collect chests with a friend, Clanmate or another player - without the risk of losing Trophies!

name: 2v2 2
tID: 2v2 Battle allows you to collect chests, earn Victory Gold and have fun with a friend, Clanmate or another player!

name: 2v2 3
tID: 2v2 Battle uses your own card collection. Matchmaking ensures that you're playing at the right skill level for you.

name: 2v2 4
tID: In 2v2 Battle, your King Level is adjusted to the average between you and your teammate.

name: 2v2 5
tID: In 2v2 Battle, your opponents are selected based on your team's skill level.

name: 2v2 6
tID: We've done the math: 2v2 Battle is at least twice the fun of anything else. Probably more.

name: take a break1
tID: If you lose a few games in a row, consider taking a break!

name: take a break2
tID: If you've been playing Clash Royale for a long time, consider taking a break!

name: 2v2 7
tID: At the end of a 2v2 Battle, you can chat with your teammate and have a rematch!

name: check shop
tID: Make sure to check the Shop each day to see what's new!

name: touchdown
tID: Touchdown is a sporty game mode... without towers! Get a troop into your opponent's end zone to score.

name: quests
tID: Quests allow you to take on daily and weekly goals to earn epic rewards.

name: gem rush
tID: When a Gem Rush event is on, you gain bonus Gems in 1v1 Arena Battles!

name: gold rush
tID: When a Gold Rush event is on, you gain bonus gold in 1v1 Arena Battles!

name: 2v2 8
tID: During a 2v2 Battle, your teammate's cards and Elixir are shown next to their name.

name: Clan wars 1
tID: On Collection Day, most battles are played using your own cards.

name: Clan wars 2
tID: On War Day, all battles are played using the Clan Cards.

name: Clan wars 3
tID: The goal on Collection Day is to collect as many Clan Cards as possible.

name: Clan wars 4
tID: The goal on War Day is to win your Final Battle! The Clan with the most Final Battle victories wins the war.

name: Clan wars 5
tID: Clan Card levels cannot be higher than your own card levels. Upgrade your own cards to use higher level Clan Cards!

name: Clan wars 6
tID: To join a Clan War, you just need to battle on Collection Day!

name: Clan wars 7
tID: All battles on Collection Day earn Clan Cards. Wins earn the most!

name: Clan wars 8
tID: Play more battles on Collection Day to earn more Clan Cards!

name: Clan wars 9
tID: Bigger Clans can earn more Clan Cards, meaning more options for your War Deck!

name: Clan wars 10
tID: The higher your Arena, the more Clan Cards you can contribute to the war!

name: Clan wars 11
tID: You'll unlock different Clan Cards in each war, so the War Day experience will be unique every time!

name: Clan wars 12
tID: On War Day, everyone in your Clan battles with the same Clan Cards.

name: Clan wars 13
tID: Share decks and chat with your Clan to create the best decks for War Day!

name: Clan wars 14
tID: Clan Cards that you've not unlocked in your own card collection cannot be used in Clan Wars.

name: Clan wars 15
tID: You need 10 participants on Collection Day to progress to War Day.

name: Clan wars 16
tID: Your Season Chest is based on the highest ranked war you participated in during the season.

name: Clan wars 17
tID: Rank higher in a war during the Clan War season to earn a bigger chest at the end of it!

name: Clan wars 18
tID: Season Chests and War Bounties get bigger in the higher Clan Leagues.

name: Clan wars 19
tID: Winning your Collection Day battles gives Victory Gold. Double on War Day!

name: Clan wars 20
tID: After a battle has been played on Collection Day, a new battle will appear on the map.

name: Clan wars 21
tID: How many Elite Barbarians does it take to hoist a sail?

name: Clan wars 22
tID: Complete your War Day Battle to earn a War Bounty!

name: Clan wars battle day 1
tID: Test your War Deck in a Friendly Battle with Clanmates before your Final Battle.

name: Clan wars battle day 2
tID: Chat with your Clan to create the best War Deck before your Final Battle.

name: Clan wars battle day 3
tID: Share decks and chat with your Clan to create the best War Deck!

name: Clan wars battle day 4
tID: Each win on War Day earns an extra Clan Trophy, meaning bigger Clans can gain more Clan Trophies!

name: Clan wars battle day 5
tID: Rank higher in a war to earn more Clan Trophies. Wins on War Day earn extra!

name: Clan wars battle day 6
tID: Make sure to cheer on your Clanmates when they play their Final Battle!

name: Clan wars battle day 7
tID: Winning your Final Battle gains a bonus Clan Trophy for your Clan!

name: Clan wars battle day 8
tID: The Clan with the most Final Battle victories wins the war!

name: Clan wars battle day 9
tID: Complete your War Day Battle to earn a War Bounty!

name: Clan wars battle day 10
tID: War Bounties contain lots of gold, and sometimes a Trade Token!

name: deck basics3
tID: Try putting a spell card in your Battle Deck to damage troops and towers from afar.

name: deck basics4
tID: Spell cards can help you damage enemy towers when your troops can't reach.

name: deck basics5
tID: Try putting a building card in your Battle Deck to help defend against Giants and Balloons.

name: bubble gum1
tID: Don't chew Double Trouble Gum while running! Unless you've had years of didgeridoo lessons.

name: bubble gum2
tID: Watch your step when walking in the woods near Royal Arena... because you may tread in some Double Trouble Gum.

name: outside clan wars1
tID: Clan Wars unlock at King Level 8.

name: outside clan wars2
tID: In Clan Wars, Clan Card levels cannot be higher than your own card levels - so your whole card collection is important.

name: outside clan wars3
tID: Clan Trophies indicate your Clan's success in Clan Wars.

name: outside clan wars4
tID: In Clan Wars, the higher your Arena, the more Clan Cards you can contribute to the war!

name: outside clan wars5
tID: Play Clan Wars to gain Clan Trophies and earn rewards!

name: outside clan wars6
tID: Winning any battle in a Clan War gives a sizeable amount of Victory Gold!

name: outside clan wars7
tID: You can find Trade Tokens by participating in Clan Wars!

name: card rarity 1
tID: Common Cards can be just as strong as Epic Cards - it's the card levels that you want to pay attention to.

name: card rarity 2
tID: A Common Card can be stronger than an Epic Card if its level is higher.

name: card rarity 5
tID: If used correctly, a Common Card can outperform a Legendary Card - it's all about positioning.

name: card rarity 6
tID: All cards are created equally - even Royal Giants.

name: max card levels
tID: All cards can be upgraded to level 13 - that's the max level!

name: tourney card levels
tID: Level 9 is the \qtournament cap\q for all cards.

name: trade tokens 1
tID: Use Trade Tokens to swap cards with your Clanmates - even Legendary Cards!

name: trade tokens 2
tID: Trade Tokens can be found in War Bounties, Challenges and the Shop.

name: goblin giant
tID: Goblin Giant carries two Spear Goblins everywhere he goes - it's a weird but functional arrangement.
